      <intermediateExchange id="3f32525f-5874-5bd4-9964-60512ae1c461" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="1310-73-2" amount="0.03271525038369869" intermediateExchangeId="61396bcb-bf35-411a-a6a6-8543ccef83e8" activityLinkId="0ff14b6a-8dcf-508f-a340-73733d530fd5">
        <name xml:lang="en">sodium hydroxide, without water, in 50% solution state</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on stoichiometric calculations and literature data. 
39.997108g/mol is the molar mass of sodium hydroxide, without water, in 50% solution state (HNaO). 
326.288462g/mol is the molar mass of triphenyl phosphate (C18H15O4P). 

Triphenyl phosphate is the result of the reaction of phosphorus oxychloride and phenol (Brooke et al. 2009). In the process 3 moles of hydrogen chloride are produced per mole of reference product.
Hydrochloric acid is produced in the reaction. Hydrochloric acid is neutralized with sodium hydroxide resulting in emissions of sodium chloride.
Chemical reaction:
POCl3 + 3 HOC6H5 -&gt; OP(OC6H5)3 + 3 HCl</comment>
